        <div n="153-009D" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-1"> A widow kept a favourite cat,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-2"> At first a gentle creature</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-3"> But w<hi rend="sup">n</hi>: he was grown sleik, and fat</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-4"> W<hi rend="sup">th</hi>: many a mouse &amp; many a rat</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-5"> He soon disclos'd his nature.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-6"> The fox &amp; he were friends of old</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-7"> Nor cou'd they now be parted</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-8"> They nightly slunk to rob y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Fold</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-9"> Devour'd y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Lambs y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Fleeces sold</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-10"> And Puss grew Lion hearted.</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-11"> He scratch <unclear>insher</unclear> maid, &amp; stole her cream,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-12"> He tore her best lac'd pinner</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-13"> Nor Chanticleer upon y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> beam</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-14"> Nor chick, nor Duckling scapes w<hi rend="sup">n</hi>: grim</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-15"> Invites y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Fox to dinner.</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-16"> The Dame full wisely did decree,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-17"> For fear he shoud dispatch more,</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-18"> y<hi rend="sup">tÌ£</hi> y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> false wretch shoud worried be</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-19"> But in a sawcy manner he</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-20"> Thus speech'd it like a Lechmore.</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-21"> Must I against all right &amp; law,</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-22"> Like Pole-cat vile be treated</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-23"> I who so long w<hi rend="sup">th</hi>: tooth &amp; claw,</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-24"> Have kept domestick mice in awe,</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-25"> And foreign rats defeated.</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-26"> Your golden pippins, and y<hi rend="sup">r</hi>: pyes</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-27"> how oft have I defended</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-28"> Tis true y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> pinner y<hi rend="sup">t</hi>: y<hi rend="sup">u</hi>: prise</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-29"> I tore in frolick to your eyes</l><l n="30" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-30"> I never harm intended.</l><l n="31" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-31"> I am a cat of honour, stay</l><l n="32" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-32"> Quoth she no longer parly</l><l n="33" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-33"> W<hi rend="sup">t</hi>: ere y<hi rend="sup">o</hi>: did in battle slay</l><l n="34" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-34"> By law of arms became y<hi rend="sup">r</hi>: prey</l><l n="35" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-35"> I hope y<hi rend="sup">o</hi>: won it fairly.</l><l n="36" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-36"> Of this we grant y<hi rend="sup">o</hi>: stand acquit</l><l n="37" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-37"> But not of y<hi rend="sup">r</hi>: outrages</l><l n="38" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-38"> Tell me perfidious was it fitt</l><l n="39" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-39"> To make my cream a perquisite</l><l n="40" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-40"> And steal to mend y<hi rend="sup">or</hi>: wages</l><l n="41" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-41"> So flagrant is thy insolence</l><l n="42" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-42"> So vile thy breach of trust is</l><l n="43" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-43"> That longer w<hi rend="sup">th</hi>: thee to dispence</l><l n="44" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-44"> Were want of power, want of sence</l><l n="45" xml:id="spp-153-009D-line-45"> Here towser do him justice.153-009D   </l></lg></div>
